<HR> <P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00135200000000000000> Rotate Operation</A></H2>
<P>
	<A NAME=est-xrot HREF="est-xrotbig.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="" SRC="est-xrot.gif"></A>
	<A HREF="est-xrotbig.gif">Figure (est-xrot): Torus Solid Edit Rotation about X</A>
<P>
<tt>mged&gt; <em>Select the ``Rotate'' entry in the solid edit menu</em> <BR>mged&gt; <em>p 45 0 0</em> <BR>mged&gt; 
</tt>
<P>
The torus is rotated 45 degrees counter-clockwise about the positive X axis.
The
coordinates of the points I and H are transformed using the following matrix:
<PRE><TT>[x'] [1   0      0   ] [x]
    [y']=[0  .7071 -.7071] [y]
    [z'] [0  .7071  .7071] [z]</TT></PRE>
See 
	<A HREF="est-xrotbig.gif">Figure (est-xrot)</A>
.
<P>
	<A NAME=est-yrot HREF="est-yrotbig.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="" SRC="est-yrot.gif"></A>
	<A HREF="est-yrotbig.gif">Figure (est-yrot): Torus Solid Edit Rotation about Y</A>
<P>
<tt>mged&gt; <em>p 0 45 0</em> <BR>mged&gt; 
</tt>
<P>
The torus is rotated 45 degrees counter-clockwise about the positive Y axis.
See 
	<A HREF="est-yrotbig.gif">Figure (est-yrot)</A>
.
<P>
	<A NAME=est-zrot HREF="est-zrotbig.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="" SRC="est-zrot.gif"></A>
	<A HREF="est-zrotbig.gif">Figure (est-zrot): Torus Solid Edit Rotation about Z</A>
<P>
<tt>mged&gt; <em>p 0 0 45</em> <BR>mged&gt; 
</tt>
<P>
The torus is rotated 45 degrees counter-clockwise about the positive Z axis.
See 
	<A HREF="est-zrotbig.gif">Figure (est-zrot)</A>
.
The original orientation is restored by entering
<P>
<tt>mged&gt; <em>p 0 0 0</em> <BR>mged&gt; 
</tt>
<P>
